abstract: >-
  OCTooL is a comprehensive software application designed for the export,
  analysis, and quantification of Optical Coherence Tomography (OCT)
  images. It provides researchers and clinicians with powerful tools to
  extract quantitative data from OCT imaging studies, including batch
  processing, interactive annotation, and advanced lesion depth detection
  algorithms.
keywords:
  - OCT
  - optical coherence tomography
  - image analysis
  - quantitative analysis
  - lesion depth
  - dental research
  - medical imaging
  - Python
  - tkinter
repository-code: "https://github.com/T0bC/OCTooL.git"
version: 2026.6
date-released: 2026-06-09
license: GPL-3.0-or-later
notes: >-
  Author contributions by module:

  - Tobias Meißner: Main developer and maintainer of OCTooL. Led
    architecture and development across all modules (Export, Analyze,
    CarlQuant), GUI design, error handling, documentation, and release
    management.

  - Maximilian Bemmann: Co-developed the prototype for the CarlQuant
    quantitative analysis module (lesion depth detection algorithms)
    during his affiliation at Leipzig University.

  - Jonas Golde: Provided the foundational OCT spectral-to-grayvalue
    conversion algorithm (originally implemented in MATLAB) that
    underpins the Export module's image reconstruction logic.

  Generative AI tools were used to assist with code generation,
  debugging, and documentation drafting during the development of this
  software. The authors reviewed all AI-generated content for
  correctness, functionality, and scientific accuracy and take full
  responsibility for the final published work. The following model(s) or
  application(s) were used: Claude Sonnet 4.6, Claude Opus 4.5, Kimi 2.5.
